defs.docs: Miscellaneous UTF-8 and UTF-16 types and methods.

defs.name: InvalidUtf16FirstUnit
defs.docs:
Cannot tell whether an `u16` needs an extra unit,
 because it's a trailing surrogate itself.

defs.name: EmptyStrError
defs.docs:
Cannot create an `Utf8Char` or `Utf16Char` from the first codepoint of a str,
 because there are none.

defs.name: NonAsciiError
defs.docs:
Cannot create an `Utf8Char` from a standalone `u8`
 that is not an ASCII character.

defs.name: NonBMPError
defs.docs:
Cannot create an `Utf16Char` from a standalone `u16` that is not a
 codepoint in the basic multilingual plane, but part of a suurrogate pair.

defs.name: Utf16Reserved
defs.docs: It's reserved for UTF-16 surrogate pairs."

defs.name: TooHigh
defs.docs: It's higher than the highest codepoint (which is 0x10ffff).

defs.name: InvalidCodepoint
defs.docs: Reasons why an `u32` is not a valid UTF codepoint.

defs.name: error_range
defs.docs: Get the range of values for which this error would be given.

defs.name: FirstIsTrailingSurrogate
defs.docs: The first unit is a trailing/low surrogate, which is never valid.

defs.name: SuperfluousSecond
defs.docs: You provided a second unit, but the first one stands on its own.

defs.name: MissingSecond
defs.docs: The first and only unit requires a second unit.

defs.name: InvalidSecond
defs.docs: The first unit requires a second unit, but it's not a trailing/low surrogate.

defs.name: InvalidUtf16Tuple
defs.docs: Reasons why one or two `u16`s are not valid UTF-16, in sinking precedence.

defs.name: EmptySlice
defs.docs: The slice is empty.

defs.name: FirstLowSurrogate
defs.docs: The first unit is a low surrogate.

defs.name: MissingSecond
defs.docs: The first and only unit requires a second unit.

defs.name: SecondNotLowSurrogate
defs.docs: The first unit requires a second one, but it's not a trailing surrogate.

defs.name: InvalidUtf16Slice
defs.docs: Reasons why a slice of `u16`s doesn't start with valid UTF-16.

defs.name: UnexpectedTrailingSurrogate
defs.docs: A trailing surrogate was not preceeded by a leading surrogate.

defs.name: UnmatchedLeadingSurrogate
defs.docs: A leading surrogate was followed by an unit that was not a trailing surrogate.

defs.name: Incomplete
defs.docs: A trailing surrogate was expected when the end was reached.

defs.name: Utf16PairError
defs.docs: Types of invalid sequences encountered by `Utf16CharParser`.

defs.name: MultipleCodepoints
defs.docs: `Utf8Char` or `Utf16Char` cannot store more than a single codepoint.

defs.name: Empty
defs.docs: `Utf8Char` or `Utf16Char` cannot be empty.

defs.name: FromStrError
defs.docs: Reasons why `Utf8Char::from_str()` or `Utf16Char::from_str()` failed.

defs.name: TooLongSeqence
defs.docs: Sequences cannot be longer than 4 bytes. Is given for values >= 240.

defs.name: ContinuationByte
defs.docs: This byte belongs to a previous sequence. Is given for values between 128 and 192 (exclusive).

defs.name: InvalidUtf8FirstByte
defs.docs: Reasons why a byte is not the start of a UTF-8 codepoint.

defs.name: FirstByte
defs.docs: Something is wrong with the first byte.

defs.name: NotAContinuationByte
defs.docs:
The byte at index 1...3 should be a continuation byte,
 but dosesn't fit the pattern 0b10xx_xxxx.

defs.name: OverLong
defs.docs: There are too many leading zeros: it could be a byte shorter.

defs.name: InvalidUtf8
defs.docs:
Reasons why a byte sequence is not valid UTF-8, excluding invalid codepoint.
 In sinking precedence.

defs.name: Utf8
defs.docs: Not a valid UTF-8 sequence.

defs.name: Codepoint
defs.docs: Not a valid unicode codepoint.

defs.name: InvalidUtf8Array
defs.docs: Reasons why a byte array is not valid UTF-8, in sinking precedence.

defs.name: Utf8
defs.docs: Something is certainly wrong with the first byte.

defs.name: Codepoint
defs.docs: The encoded codepoint is invalid:

defs.name: TooShort
defs.docs: The slice is too short; n bytes was required.

defs.name: InvalidUtf8Slice
defs.docs: Reasons why a byte slice is not valid UTF-8, in sinking precedence.

defs.name: U8UtfExt
defs.docs: Methods for working with `u8`s as UTF-8 bytes.

defs.name: extra_utf8_bytes
defs.docs: How many more bytes will you need to complete this codepoint?

defs.name: extra_utf8_bytes_unchecked
defs.docs: How many more bytes will you need to complete this codepoint?

defs.name: U16UtfExt
defs.docs: Methods for working with `u16`s as UTF-16 units.

defs.name: utf16_needs_extra_unit
defs.docs: Will you need an extra unit to complete this codepoint?

defs.name: is_utf16_leading_surrogate
defs.docs:
Does this `u16` need another `u16` to complete a codepoint?
 Returns `(self & 0xfc00) == 0xd800`

defs.name: CharExt
defs.docs: Extension trait for `char` that adds methods for converting to and from UTF-8 or UTF-16.

defs.name: to_utf8
defs.docs: Get the UTF-8 representation of this codepoint.

defs.name: to_utf16
defs.docs: Get the UTF-16 representation of this codepoint.

defs.name: iter_utf8_bytes
defs.docs:
Iterate over or [read](https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/io/trait.Read.html)
 the one to four bytes in the UTF-8 representation of this codepoint.

defs.name: iter_utf16_units
defs.docs: Iterate over the one or two units in the UTF-16 representation of this codepoint.

defs.name: to_utf8_array
defs.docs:
Convert this char to an UTF-8 array, and also return how many bytes of
 the array are used,

defs.name: to_utf16_tuple
defs.docs:
Convert this `char` to UTF-16.
 The second `u16` is `Some` if a surrogate pair is required.

defs.name: from_utf8_slice_start
defs.docs:
Create a `char` from the start of an UTF-8 slice,
 and also return how many bytes were used.

defs.name: from_utf16_slice_start
defs.docs:
Create a `char` from the start of an UTF-16 slice,
 and also return how many units were used.

defs.name: from_utf8_array
defs.docs: Convert an UTF-8 sequence as returned from `.to_utf8_array()` into a `char`

defs.name: from_utf16_tuple
defs.docs: Convert a UTF-16 pair as returned from `.to_utf16_tuple()` into a `char`.

defs.name: from_utf8_exact_slice_unchecked
defs.docs: Convert an UTF-8 sequence into a char.

defs.name: from_utf16_tuple_unchecked
defs.docs: Convert a UTF-16 tuple as returned from `.to_utf16_tuple()` into a `char`.

defs.name: from_u32_detailed
defs.docs: Perform some extra validations compared to `char::from_u32_unchecked()`

defs.name: StrExt
defs.docs: Adds `.utf8chars()` and `.utf16chars()` iterator constructors to `&str`.

defs.name: utf8chars
defs.docs: Equivalent to `.chars()` but produces `Utf8Char`s.

defs.name: utf16chars
defs.docs: Equivalent to `.chars()` but produces `Utf16Char`s.

defs.name: utf8char_indices
defs.docs: Equivalent to `.char_indices()` but produces `Utf8Char`s.

defs.name: utf16char_indices
defs.docs: Equivalent to `.char_indices()` but produces `Utf16Char`s.

defs.name: IterExt
defs.docs: Iterator methods that convert between `u8`s and `Utf8Char` or `u16`s and `Utf16Char`

defs.name: to_bytes
defs.docs:
Converts an iterator of `Utf8Char`s or `&Utf8Char`s to an iterator of
 `u8`s.

defs.name: to_units
defs.docs:
Converts an iterator of `Utf16Char` (or `&Utf16Char`) to an iterator of
 `u16`s.

defs.name: to_utf8chars
defs.docs: Decodes bytes as UTF-8 and groups them into `Utf8Char`s

defs.name: to_utf16chars
defs.docs: Decodes bytes as UTF-16 and groups them into `Utf16Char`s

defs.name: SliceExt
defs.docs: Methods for iterating over `u8` and `u16` slices as UTF-8 or UTF-16 characters.

defs.name: utf8char_indices
defs.docs: Decode `u8` slices as UTF-8 and iterate over the codepoints as `Utf8Char`s,

defs.name: utf16char_indices
defs.docs: Decode `u16` slices as UTF-16 and iterate over the codepoints as `Utf16Char`s,

defs.name: from_slice_start
defs.docs:
Create an `Utf8Char` of the first codepoint in an UTF-8 slice.  
 Also returns the length of the UTF-8 sequence for the codepoint.

defs.name: from_slice_start_unchecked
defs.docs: A `from_slice_start()` that doesn't validate the codepoint.

defs.name: from_array
defs.docs: Create an `Utf8Char` from a byte array after validating it.

defs.name: from_array_unchecked
defs.docs: Zero-cost constructor.

defs.name: from_ascii
defs.docs: Create an `Utf8Char` from a single byte.

defs.name: from_ascii_unchecked
defs.docs:
Create an `Utf8Char` from a single byte without checking that it's a
 valid codepoint on its own, which is only true for ASCII characters.

Converts an iterator of `Utf8Char` (or `&Utf8Char`)
 to an iterator of `u8`s.  
 Is equivalent to calling `.flat_map()` on the original iterator,
 but the returned iterator is ~40% faster.
